<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
BARRON, AMAR LEAD SANTA CLARA OVER AGOURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Art Barron scored 19 points and Steve Amar added 16 to pace host Santa Clara 
High to an 81-63 nonleague victory over Agoura on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
With the win, the Saints improve to 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura's Sean Martin scored a game-high 33 points. 
</P>
<P>
In other boys' basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 97, Calabasas 78 -- Chris Loll scored 25 points and Brian Capella 
finished with 24 to lead the Lancers against Calabasas in the first round of 
the Thousand Oaks tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Hoover scored a game-high 32 points and Jason Young finished with 19 for 
Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
Hoover 71, San Marino 41 -- Dave Ulloa scored 22 points and Gabe Alvarado added 
15 to pace the Tornadoes' nonleague victory against visiting San Marino (1-4). 
</P>
<P>
Hoover (4-2) jumped out to a 39-17 lead at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley 80, Apple Valley 45 -- Willie Montgomery scored a game-high 16 
points to lead Antelope Valley in a nonleague game at home. 
</P>
<P>
Reynell Dunbar had 12 points for Antelope Valley (3-5), which raced to a 35-11 
lead at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Faith Baptist 63, Fillmore 54 -- Alex Estrada scored 27 points and made 13 of 
15 free throws as Faith Baptist (5-1) won a nonleague game at Fillmore. 
</P>
<P>
Peter Rasmussen had 18 points and 15 rebounds for the winners. Richard Aguilera 
led Fillmore (4-2) with 25 points. 
</P>
<P>
Campbell Hall 57, Cantwell 42 -- Off-guard Austin McKellar scored a game-high 
18 points and added seven rebounds to lead the Vikings in a nonleague game. 
</P>
<P>
C. J. Thompkins had 17 points and seven assists for visiting Campbell Hall 
(5-0) and freshman center Alex Lopez added 12 points and 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Rio Hondo Prep 73, Providence 66 -- Todd Carson scored 32 points to pace Rio 
Hondo Prep's nonleague victory at Providence. 
</P>
<P>
Brett Ferrante led the Pioneers with 16 points, followed by Chris Jones with 
14. 
</P>
<P>
Rosemead 74, Montclair Prep 61 -- Joe Diep's 32 points helped Rosemead (4-1) 
defeat the Mounties (6-2) in a semifinal game of the Flintridge Prep 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The Mounties, who trailed, 36-31, at halftime, were led by J. T. Billingslea, 
who scored 15 points. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Sanger had 12 points and 10 rebounds and Kris Johnson added 10 points and 
15 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Highland Hall 78, Hillcrest Christian 61 -- John Klejnot scored 38 points and 
grabbed 15 rebounds to pace host Highland Hall (3-2, 1-0) in a Westside League 
game. 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade 62, L.A. Baptist 54 -- Richard Fei scored a game-high 19 points to 
lead Chaminade in a nonleague game. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Holland added 12 points for Chaminade. Dan Shackelford (17 points) and 
Alex Pistone (14) led L. A. Baptist (0-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
