<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPRINGER WINS 2 TITLES IN TENNIS COMPETITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tom Springer of Canoga Park won a pair of titles to lead a successful 
Valley-area contingent in the eighth Rancho Bernardo Inn Senior Grand Prix 
Masters Tennis Championships in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
After winning the men's age 55-and-older singles title, Springer teamed with 
Gary Russell of Rancho Palos Verdes to post another victory in the doubles 
competition. 
</P>
<P>
In singles action, Shannon Gordon of Van Nuys won the women's 30-and-over title 
and Art Santilli of Camarillo took home the men's 40-plus trophy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
