<HEADLINE>
<P>
5 PILGRIMS DIE IN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MEXICO CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Five people died and at least 12 people were injured Tuesday when a bus 
carrying pilgrims to celebrate the anniversary of the sighting of Mexico's 
Virgin of Guadalupe crashed head-on into a truck en route to Mexico City, 
police said. Every year hundreds of thousands of worshipers flock to the shrine 
of the Virgin of Guadalupe, who was first sighted on a Mexican Indian's tunic 
on Dec. 12, 1531. 
</P>
