<P>
Seven streets will be closed in about two weeks with temporary wooden 
barricades as part of a 90-day trial program, officials said. The affected 
streets are National Avenue, McFarlane Avenue, Warner Boulevard, Toluca Lake 
Avenue, Franklin Avenue and Hood Avenue between Rose Street and Olive/Pass 
avenues, and Rose Street between Lakeside Drive and Hood Avenue. 
