<HEADLINE>
<P>
FILLIES VIE IN ALTHEA TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There will be a rare weekday stakes race at Hollywood Park today. 
</P>
<P>
Seven 2-year-old fillies will compete in the $50,450 Althea Stakes, and the 
probable favorite in the 1 1/16-mile turf race is Dorky, who is dropping in 
class after finishing seventh in the Hollywood Starlet. 
</P>
<P>
The other entrants are Saratoga Success, Hit a Homer Honey, Assombrie, Serious 
Toy, Ten Hail Marys and Spirited Susan. BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
