<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: RADIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Operation Mark and Brian: KLOS-FM (95.5) morning drive-time duo Mark Thompson 
and Brian Phelps will broadcast their top-rated show from Saudi Arabia on 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
They'll make the 18-hour flight Monday on MGM Air as part of Operation Desert 
Cheer, which is transporting 15 tons of gifts for the servicemen. A satellite 
hook-up costing an estimated $15,000 will enable Tuesday's show to be heard 
live in Southern California. The pair hope to be able to broadcast telephone 
calls between servicemen and their families in the Los Angeles area. The 
usually irreverent deejays grew serious on the air Tuesday discussing their 
impending trip. "It's absolutely mind-boggling for us, a great honor," said 
Thompson. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
