<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Matt Lait and Herman Wong 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHOOTING STARS: The current issue of Discover magazine pays homage to Orange 
County Astronomers, the largest group of amateurs in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
With 600 members and an observatory near Mt. Palomar, the club has provided the 
magazine with spectacular color photographs of a comet, a solar prominence and 
several nebulae. . . . "As professional astronomers produce fewer and fewer 
pictures, amateurs are increasingly turning out stunning ones," says the 
article. It calls the club's 22-inch telescope "an amateur astronomer's dream." 
Matt Lait and Herman Wong 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
