<P>
BLINDER RACKS VOTED FOR SEX PUBLICATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has passed a law requiring merchants to cover the lower 
two-thirds of all sexually explicit materials. 
</P>
<P>
The law passed 4 to 0 and will be in effect in 30 days. Violation is a 
misdemeanor. 
</P>
<P>
Councilwoman Marilyn Bruce Hastings said the ordinance was prompted by 
complaints from residents about sexually explicit magazines at liquor stores 
and easily visible videos. 
</P>
<P>
Other cities in Orange County have passed similar ordinances. 
</P>
