CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
MEYERS; 
</P>
<P>
STATE TRIES BLASTERS TO DISLODGE SNOWPACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Frustrated by the poor performance of 75-millimeter cannons in an effort to 
shoot down avalanches in the Sierra Nevada, state transportation officials are 
trying gas blasters triggered by remote control. 
</P>
<P>
Caltrans says that five of the curved, 17-foot blasters have been installed in 
steep terrain over U.S. 50 on Echo Summit. The area, just west of Lake Tahoe 
and about 90 miles east of Sacramento, is often hit by avalanches. Four more 
gas blasters are to be installed by next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
