<P>
N. HOLLYWOOD DRUG LAB RAIDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Narcotics agents and police raided an active drug lab capable of producing at 
least $1 million worth of crystal methamphetamine, or "ice," and arrested four 
Korean gang members, officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
Agents from the U.S. Drug Enforcement Administration and the state Bureau of 
Narcotics Enforcement and Los Angeles police raided a North Hollywood apartment 
about 7:35 p.m. Tuesday, DEA spokesman Ralph Lochridge said. 
</P>
<P>
The officers arrested four adults described as Korean gang members, Lochridge 
said. Their identities were not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
The potent smokable form of methamphetamine, worth about $100,000 per pound on 
the street, is in great demand in Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
Lochridge said the North Hollywood raid was the first documented case of "ice" 
manufacturing by Koreans in Los Angeles for distribution in Hawaii. 
</P>
</TEXT>
