SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
RIGBY FLIES HIGH IN 'PETER PAN' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former gymnastics star Cathy Rigby says making her Broadway debut in "Peter 
Pan" is like old times. 
</P>
<P>
"This is like the Olympics of theater," Rigby said in an interview Tuesday. 
"You have all those same feelings of excitement." 
</P>
<P>
Rigby, who won a silver medal at the World Gymnastics Championships in 1970, 
took up acting and singing after retiring from competition. 
</P>
<P>
The 36-year-old mother of four has been on the road for a year in the revival 
of the musical about the boy who refuses to grow up. The show opens on Broadway 
on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Cathy Rigby soars through the air in "Peter Pan" performance. United 
Press International 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
